Nineteen (38%) patients died during follow-up. Table 4
lists the causes of death among transplanted patients. Five (10%) patients relapsed during the follow-up period with a median time to relapse of 4 months (range, 1 to 9 months). Six-month OS, RFS, CIR, and NRM were 73.9%, 57%, 10.2%, and 19.4%, respectively. No significant differences were found in OS (P = .411) and progression-free survival (P = .563) between patients in CR1 versus CR2 versus active disease. One-year OS, RFS, CIR, and NRM were 48.1%, 35.7%, 16%, and 38.2%, respectively (Table 2). Causes of death were relapse in 4 (8%) cases, graft failure in 2 (4%) patients, infection in 9 (18%) patients, multiorgan failure in 2 (4%) cases, acute GVHD in 1 case, and cardiac arrhythmia in 1 case (Figure 2, Figure 3, Figure 4
).
